{"type":"message","id":"693469b1","parentId":"49381aca","timestamp":"2026-03-10T00:27:19.247Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Mon 2026-03-09 19:27 EST] [Subagent Context] You are running as a subagent (depth 1/1). Results auto-announce to your requester; do not busy-poll for status.\n\n[Subagent Task]: # TASK: Integrate Real Monitoring System into OpenClaw Workflows\n\n## CONTEXT\nThe `agent-watchdog` skill now has REAL monitoring infrastructure:\n- `~/.openclaw/workspace/.watchdog/` directory with real data\n- Real session discovery and tracking\n- Observable logs and metrics\n- Real stall detection and recovery\n\n## YOUR MISSION\nIntegrate this REAL monitoring system into existing OpenClaw workflows.\n\n## SPECIFIC REQUIREMENTS\n\n### 1. Integrate with Main Agent Workflows\n- Add monitoring registration to main agent task execution\n- Track main agent sessions and sub-agent spawns\n- Monitor task progress and completion\n- Detect stalls in main agent operations\n\n### 2. Integrate with Sub-agent System\n- Register sub-agents with watchdog when spawned\n- Track sub-agent execution time and progress\n- Monitor for sub-agent stalls\n- Enable recovery for stalled sub-agents\n\n### 3. Integrate with Cron Jobs\n- Monitor cron job executions\n- Track cron job success/failure\n- Detect stalled cron jobs\n- Enable recovery for failed cron jobs\n\n### 4. Create Monitoring Dashboard\n- Simple dashboard showing system health\n- Active sessions and their status\n- Recent incidents and recoveries\n- Performance metrics\n\n### 5. Enable Real-time Alerts\n- Alert for critical stalls (>5 minutes)\n- Alert for repeated failures\n- Alert for system resource issues\n- Integration with error-learning-loop\n\n## ANTI-SIMULATION RULES\n- NO simulated monitoring integration\n- REAL session registration required\n- REAL progress tracking required\n- REAL alert generation required\n- Observable evidence required\n\n## INTEGRATION POINTS TO MODIFY\n\n### 1. Main Agent Integration\n- Modify main agent to register with watchdog\n- Add monitoring calls to task execution\n- Enable stall detection for long operations\n\n### 2. Sub-agent Spawn Integration\n- Modify `sessions_spawn` to register sub-agents\n- Add monitoring to sub-agent execution\n- Enable recovery for stalled sub-agents\n\n### 3. Cron Job Integration\n- Add monitoring to cron job execution\n- Track cron job performance\n- Enable recovery for failed cron jobs\n\n## FILES TO CREATE/MODIFY\n1. `integration/main_agent_monitoring.py` - Main agent integration\n2. `integration/subagent_monitoring.py` - Sub-agent integration\n3. `integration/cron_monitoring.py` - Cron job integration\n4. `dashboard/monitoring_dashboard.py` - Simple dashboard\n5. `alerts/real_time_alerts.py` - Alert system\n6. Update existing workflows to include monitoring\n\n## DELIVERABLES\n1. **Integrated monitoring system** working with all workflows\n2. **Evidence** showing:\n   - Main agent sessions being monitored\n   - Sub-agents registered and tracked\n   - Cron jobs monitored\n   - Real alerts generated\n   - Recovery actions triggered\n3. **Monitoring dashboard** showing real data\n4. **Handoff report** with integration evidence\n\n## SUCCESS CRITERIA\nMonitoring is **FULLY INTEGRATED** when:\n1. Main agent workflows include monitoring\n2. Sub-agents are automatically registered\n3. Cron jobs are monitored\n4. Real alerts work\n5. Dashboard shows real monitoring data\n\n## TIMELINE\n- Start: Immediate\n- Complete: Within 30 minutes\n- Report: Concise handoff with integration evidence\n\nProceed to integrate REAL monitoring into all OpenClaw workflows."}],"timestamp":1773102439244}}
