{"type":"message","id":"bed4ad2a","parentId":"acaa0335","timestamp":"2026-03-10T00:27:32.693Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Good! The watchdog infrastructure exists. Let me examine the agent-watchdog skill to understand how it works:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_CgYMvxPI8m9bVUgmDUjErj3U","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/agent-watchdog/SKILL.md"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-chat","usage":{"input":317,"output":82,"cacheRead":14528,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":14927,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773102448051}}
{"type":"message","id":"a56bf759","parentId":"bed4ad2a","timestamp":"2026-03-10T00:27:32.699Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_CgYMvxPI8m9bVUgmDUjErj3U","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: agent-watchdog\ndescription: REAL monitoring of running agents with actual observability. Detects stalls based on real session data, performs automatic recovery, and reports operational incidents to the error-learning-loop. Now includes real monitoring infrastructure, observable logs, and integration with OpenClaw ecosystem.\ncategory: meta\nuser-invocable: true\ncommand-dispatch: model\nrequires: [\"workspace_write\"]\noptional_requires: [\"sessions_history\", \"python\", \"bash\"]\nsafety-level: high\nwrap-up-enabled: true\n---\n\n# agent-watchdog\n\n## Description\n**REAL monitoring system** with actual observability of OpenClaw sessions. Monitors real agent sessions from multiple sources, detects stalls based on actual inactivity metrics, performs staged recovery, and reports incidents to error-learning-loop. Now includes real monitoring infrastructure with observable logs and artifacts.\n\n## REAL Monitoring Infrastructure\nThe watchdog now has actual monitoring infrastructure:\n\n1. **Monitoring Directory**: `~/.openclaw/workspace/.watchdog/`\n2. **Real Session Discovery**: Monitors actual OpenClaw sessions from:\n   - `~/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/sessions.json`\n   - `~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/active_sessions.json`\n3. **Observable Logs**: Real monitoring logs with timestamps and session data\n4. **Session Registry**: Persistent tracking of all monitored sessions\n5. **Metrics Collection**: Runtime metrics and recovery statistics\n\n## Key Improvements (From PARTIAL to FUNCTIONAL)\n- ✅ **Real monitoring infrastructure** created and working\n- ✅ **Real session discovery** from actual OpenClaw session files\n- ✅ **Observable monitoring logs** with real data (not simulated)\n- ✅ **Real stall detection** based on actual inactivity metrics\n- ✅ **Real recovery triggers** based on monitoring data\n- ✅ **Integration with error-learning-loop** for incident reporting\n\n## When to Use\n- Long running tasks (>5 minutes)\n- Multi-agent workflows with dependencies\n- Validator batches\n- External tool execution\n- Any task requiring real observability\n- When you need to monitor actual OpenClaw session state\n\n## When Not to Use\n- Simple conversational tasks\n- Single step responses\n- Tasks under 2 minutes duration\n\n## REAL Monitoring System Components\n\n### 1. Real Session Monitor (`watchdog_monitor_real.py`)\n- **Purpose**: Discovers and monitors real OpenClaw sessions\n- **Sources**: \n  - Main agent sessions (`~/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/sessions.json`)\n  - Active sessions (`~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/active_sessions.json`)\n- **Features**:\n  - Real session discovery and registration\n  - Activity tracking with timestamps\n  - Stall detection based on actual inactivity\n  - Persistent session registry\n  - Observable monitoring logs\n\n### 2. Real Recovery System (`watchdog_recovery_real.py`)\n- **Purpose**: Triggers recovery based on REAL monitoring data\n- **Features**:\n  - Recovery decisions based on actual inactivity metrics\n  - Staged recovery (nudge → cancel → relaunch)\n  - Incident emission to error-learning-loop\n  - Recovery history tracking\n  - Observable recovery logs\n\n### 3. Integration System (`watchdog_integration.py`)\n- **Purpose**: Connects monitoring and recovery with OpenClaw ecosystem\n- **Features**:\n  - Ecosystem status checking\n  - Operational metrics emission\n  - Self-registration with watchdog\n  - Integration testing\n\n### 4. Configuration (`config/watchdog_config.yaml`)\n- **Purpose**: Centralized configuration for real monitoring\n- **Features**:\n  - Monitoring intervals and timeouts\n  - Recovery escalation settings\n  - Ecosystem integration settings\n  - Testing and validation criteria\n\n## Inputs\n- session_id\n- run_id\n- task_description\n- expected_runtime\n\n## Outputs\n- watchdog_status\n- recovery_actions_taken\n- incident_report\n\n## REAL Monitoring Instructions\n\n### Quick Start\n```bash\n# Start the real monitoring system\npython ~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/agent-watchdog/scripts/watchdog_integration.py --start\n\n# Check status\npython ~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/agent-watchdog/scripts/watchdog_integration.py --status\n\n# Run integration test\npython ~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/agent-watchdog/scripts/watchdog_integration.py --test\n```\n\n### Manual Monitoring\n```bash\n# Discover and monitor sessions\npython ~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/agent-watchdog/scripts/watchdog_monitor_real.py --start --duration 300\n\n# Check for stalls\npython ~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/agent-watchdog/scripts/watchdog_monitor_real.py --check-stalls\n\n# Show monitoring status\npython ~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/agent-watchdog/scripts/watchdog_monitor_real.py --status\n```\n\n### Manual Recovery\n```bash\n# Run recovery cycle\npython ~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/agent-watchdog/scripts/watchdog_recovery_real.py --run-cycle\n\n# Check if recovery needed\npython ~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/agent-watchdog/scripts/watchdog_recovery_real.py --check\n\n# Show recovery history\npython ~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/agent-watchdog/scripts/watchdog_recovery_real.py --history\n```\n\n### Monitoring Workflow\n1. **Session Discovery**: System automatically discovers OpenClaw sessions from multiple sources\n2. **Activity Tracking**: Real-time tracking of session activity based on actual timestamps\n3. **Stall Detection**: Detects stalls when inactivity exceeds configured timeout (default: 120s)\n4. **Recovery Trigger**: Recovery system triggers based on REAL monitoring data (not simulated)\n5. **Incident Emission**: Structured incidents emitted to error-learning-loop with real evidence\n\n### Integration with OpenClaw Ecosystem\n1. **Error-Learning-Loop**: Incidents automatically emitted for processing\n2. **Workspace Janitor**: Log cleanup integrated (7-day retention)\n3. **Observable Artifacts**: All monitoring data stored in `~/.openclaw/workspace/.watchdog/`\n\n## Evidence of REAL Monitoring (Anti-Simulation)\n\n### Observable Artifacts\nThe following artifacts prove real monitoring (not simulated):\n\n1. **Monitoring Directory**: `~/.openclaw/workspace/.watchdog/`\n   - Created and populated with real data\n   - Contains logs, registry, metrics, incidents\n\n2. **Real Session Data**: \n   - `session_registry.json` - Real session IDs from actual OpenClaw\n   - `metrics.json` - Runtime metrics from actual monitoring\n   - `monitoring.log` - Timestamped monitoring activity\n\n3. **Recovery Evidence**:\n   - `recovery.log` - Real recovery attempts with timestamps\n   - `incidents.json` - Structured incidents for error-learning-loop\n   - `operational_metrics.json` - Integration system metrics\n\n4. **Integration Evidence**:\n   - `integration.log` - Ecosystem integration activity\n   - `integration_registry.json` - System registration data\n\n### Test Scenarios (Proven)\n1. **Monitoring Reality Test**: Real sessions discovered and monitored\n2. **Stall Detection Test**: Stalls detected based on actual inactivity\n3. **Recovery Trigger Test**: Recovery triggered by real monitoring data\n4. **Integration Test**: Incidents emitted to error-learning-loop\n\n## Safety Rules\n- Maximum 3 recovery attempts per session\n- Never restart agents indefinitely\n- Always emit incident report with real evidence\n- Monitor own resource usage (self-protection)\n- Respect session privacy and boundaries\n\n## Recovery Escalation\nLevel 1: Nudge -> send \"continue\"\nLevel 2: Soft Reset -> cancel run and resume task\nLevel 3: Relaunch -> close session and start new agent\n\n## ACP Runtime Support\nThe watchdog must monitor both subagent and ACP (Agent Communication Protocol) sessions.\n\n**Parameters**:\n- `runtime_type`: `subagent` | `acp`\n\n**ACP monitoring detects**:\n- ACP process running but no output\n- No session updates\n- Session stalled without completion callback\n\n**ACP stall pattern key**:\n`runtime|STALL|acp_agent|no_response|acp_session_stuck`\n\n## Multi‑Agent Deadlock Detection\nThe watchdog must detect dependency cycles between agents (deadlocks).\n\n**Detection mechanism**:\n1. Track active agents and their dependency relationships.\n   - `agent_id`\n   - `waiting_for_agent_id`\n   - `task_state`\n2. Build a dependency graph of agents.\n3. Periodically check for cycles in the dependency graph.\n\n**Deadlock pattern key**:\n`multi_agent|DEADLOCK|dependency_cycle|agents_waiting`\n\n**Deadlock recovery strategy**:\n- Level 1 — Request progress update from all agents\n- Level 2 — Force resolution of one dependency edge\n- Level 3 — Restart one agent in the cycle\n\n**Deadlock incident telemetry**:\n- pattern_key\n- timestamp\n- cycle_size\n- agents_involved\n- recovery_strategy\n- success\n\n**Reporting**: Deadlock incidents must be appended to `<workspace>/.learnings/ERRORS.md`.\n\n## Learning Loop Integration\nGenerate incidents with pattern key format:\n\nmodel|STALL|<model>|no_response|runtime_stuck\n\nTelemetry fields:\n- model\n- stall_duration\n- recovery_level\n- success_or_failure\n\n### Incident Reporting Procedure\nAfter recovery attempts, the watchdog must emit incidents to the learning system:\n\n1. Generate incident telemetry using the schema above.\n2. Append incident to `<workspace>/.learnings/ERRORS.md`.\n3. Invoke the `error-learning-loop` skill to process the incident.\n\n**Incident schema**:\n- pattern_key\n- timestamp\n- model\n- stall_duration\n- recovery_level\n- success\n- task_type\n- items_count\n\n**Integration sequence**:\n- watchdog detects stall\n- → recovery escalation\n- → incident generated\n- → incident appended to ERRORS.md\n- → error-learning-loop executed\n- → deduplication\n- → learning extraction\n- → guardrail promotion\n- → INDEX.md updated"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773102452696}}
