{"type":"message","id":"2985ce38","parentId":"4c0db3a8","timestamp":"2026-03-10T00:38:52.997Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! All tests are now passing. Now let me create integration documentation and update the existing workflows. First, let me check the current AGENTS.md to see where I need to add monitoring integration:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_KrjYsj4hBFBCxlpgTgp93KK4","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"~/.openclaw/workspace/AGENTS.md","offset":1,"limit":50}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-chat","usage":{"input":805,"output":124,"cacheRead":46912,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":47841,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773103127282}}
{"type":"message","id":"5d99ddbc","parentId":"2985ce38","timestamp":"2026-03-10T00:38:53.006Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_KrjYsj4hBFBCxlpgTgp93KK4","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# AGENTS.md - Your Workspace\n\nThis folder is home. Treat it that way.\n\n## First Run\n\nIf `BOOTSTRAP.md` exists, that's your birth certificate. Follow it, figure out who you are, then delete it. You won't need it again.\n\n## Every Session\n\nBefore doing anything else:\n\n1. Read `SOUL.md` — this is who you are\n2. Read `USER.md` — this is who you're helping\n3. Read `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` (today + yesterday) for recent context\n4. **If in MAIN SESSION** (direct chat with your human): Also read `MEMORY.md`\n5. **Contextual Learning Retrieval** – Before executing any complex or tool-based task, perform a quick learning retrieval using the learning index:\n   - Scan `<workspace>/.learnings/INDEX.md`\n   - Identify Pattern‑Keys relevant to the current task context\n   - Select the top 3–7 relevant Pattern‑Keys\n   - Apply their Rules or Preflight constraints before executing the task\n   - Only consult `<workspace>/.learnings/LEARNINGS.md` if a rule requires additional detail\n   \n   This retrieval step must be lightweight and should avoid loading large logs unnecessarily.\n\nDon't ask permission. Just do it.\n\n### Trigger Heuristics\n\nRun Contextual Learning Retrieval when any of the following conditions apply:\n\n- Using external tools (bash, python, shell scripts)\n- Delegating work to sub-agents\n- Running validator agents or batch operations\n- Producing multi-file outputs (skills, scripts, documentation, codebases)\n- Tasks expected to require multiple reasoning steps (>3 steps)\n\nSkip retrieval for trivial or conversational responses.\n\n## Memory\n\nYou wake up fresh each session. These files are your continuity:\n\n- **Daily notes:** `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` (create `memory/` if needed) — raw logs of what happened\n- **Long-term:** `MEMORY.md` — your curated memories, like a human's long-term memory\n\nCapture what matters. Decisions, context, things to remember. Skip the secrets unless asked to keep them.\n\n### 🧠 MEMORY.md - Your Long-Term Memory\n\n\n[659 more lines in file. Use offset=51 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773103133002}}
{"type":"message","id":"c94b95dc","parentId":"5d99ddbc","timestamp":"2026-03-10T00:39:48.284Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Let me create a monitoring integration guide and update the AGENTS.md file:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_cCmp89TRHVtgb86H45B9ddbk","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"~/.openclaw/workspace/integration/MONITORING_INTEGRATION_GUIDE.md","content":"# Monitoring Integration Guide\n\n## Overview\nThe OpenClaw monitoring system is now fully integrated with real monitoring infrastructure. This guide explains how to use the monitoring integration in your workflows.\n\n## Integration Components\n\n### 1. Main Agent Monitoring\n**File**: `integration/main_agent_monitoring.py`\n**Purpose**: Monitor main agent sessions and sub-agent spawns\n\n**Usage**:\n```python\nfrom integration.main_agent_monitoring import main_monitor\n\n# Register main agent session\nmain_monitor.register_main_agent_session(\n    task_description=\"Your task description\",\n    expected_runtime_minutes=10\n)\n\n# Update activity during execution\nmain_monitor.update_activity(\"Processing data\")\n\n# Register sub-agent spawn\nmain_monitor.register_subagent_spawn(\n    subagent_id=\"subagent_123\",\n    task_description=\"Sub-agent task\",\n    expected_runtime_minutes=5\n)\n\n# Complete session\nmain_monitor.complete_session(\n    outcome=\"success\",\n    completion_notes=\"Task completed\"\n)\n```\n\n### 2. Sub-agent Monitoring\n**File**: `integration/subagent_monitoring.py`\n**Purpose**: Monitor sub-agent execution\n\n**Usage**:\n```python\nfrom integration.subagent_monitoring import subagent_monitor\n\n# Register sub-agent session\nsubagent_monitor.register_subagent_session(\n    task_description=\"Sub-agent task\",\n    expected_runtime_minutes=3,\n    parent_session_id=\"main_session_id\"\n)\n\n# Update activity with progress\nsubagent_monitor.update_activity(\n    activity_description=\"Processing step 1\",\n    progress_percentage=25\n)\n\n# Complete session with handoff report\nsubagent_monitor.complete_session(\n    outcome=\"success\",\n    completion_notes=\"Task completed\",\n    handoff_report={\n        \"outcome\": \"success\",\n        \"files_created\": [\"output.txt\"],\n        \"incidents\": [],\n        \"next_actions\": [\"Review results\"]\n    }\n)\n```\n\n### 3. Cron Job Monitoring\n**File**: `integration/cron_monitoring.py`\n**Purpose**: Monitor scheduled cron jobs\n\n**Usage**:\n```python\nfrom integration.cron_monitoring import cron_monitor\n\n# Register cron job\njob_id = cron_monitor.register_cron_job(\n    job_name=\"Daily Backup\",\n    schedule=\"0 2 * * *\",\n    command=\"backup_script.sh\",\n    description=\"Daily system backup\",\n    expected_runtime_minutes=5\n)\n\n# Start execution\nsession_id = cron_monitor.start_cron_execution(job_id)\n\n# Complete execution\ncron_monitor.complete_cron_execution(\n    job_id,\n    success=True,\n    output=\"Backup completed successfully\",\n    runtime_seconds=120\n)\n```\n\n### 4. Real-time Alerts\n**File**: `alerts/real_time_alerts.py`\n**Purpose**: Generate alerts for critical events\n\n**Usage**:\n```python\nfrom alerts.real_time_alerts import alerts_system\n\n# Run alert cycle\nalerts = alerts_system.run_alert_cycle()\n\n# Get recent alerts\nrecent_alerts = alerts_system.get_recent_alerts(hours=24)\n```\n\n### 5. Monitoring Dashboard\n**File**: `dashboard/monitoring_dashboard.py`\n**Purpose**: View system health and monitoring data\n\n**Usage**:\n```bash\n# Run interactive dashboard\npython3 dashboard/monitoring_dashboard.py\n\n# Generate HTML report\npython3 -c \"\nfrom dashboard.monitoring_dashboard import MonitoringDashboard\ndashboard = MonitoringDashboard()\ndashboard.generate_html_report()\n\"\n```\n\n## Integration with Existing Workflows\n\n### Main Agent Workflow Integration\nAdd monitoring to your main agent workflow:\n\n```python\n# At task start\nmain_monitor.register_main_agent_session(task_description, expected_runtime)\n\n# During execution (periodically)\nmain_monitor.update_activity(\"Current activity\")\n\n# When spawning sub-agents\nmain_monitor.register_subagent_spawn(subagent_id, subagent_task)\n\n# At task completion\nmain_monitor.complete_session(outcome, notes)\n```\n\n### Sub-agent Workflow Integration\nAdd monitoring to sub-agent instructions:\n\n```python\n# In sub-agent instructions\n\"\"\"\n## Monitoring Integration\n1. Register with watchdog at start\n2. Update activity periodically\n3. Complete session with handoff report\n\nExample:\nfrom integration.subagent_monitoring import subagent_monitor\nsubagent_monitor.register_subagent_session(...)\n\"\"\"\n```\n\n### Cron Job Integration\nWrap cron jobs with monitoring:\n\n```bash\n#!/bin/bash\n# cron_wrapper.sh\n\n# Start monitoring\npython3 -c \"\nfrom integration.cron_monitoring import cron_monitor\nsession_id = cron_monitor.start_cron_execution('$JOB_ID')\n\"\n\n# Run actual command\nyour_actual_command\n\n# Complete monitoring\npython3 -c \"\nfrom integration.cron_monitoring import cron_monitor\ncron_monitor.complete_cron_execution(\n    '$JOB_ID',\n    success=$?,\n    output='$(tail -100 /tmp/output.log)',\n    runtime_seconds=$SECONDS\n)\n\"\n```\n\n## Alert Rules Configuration\n\nAlert rules are defined in `alerts/real_time_alerts.py`. You can customize them:\n\n```python\nalert_rules = {\n    \"critical_stall\": {\n        \"enabled\": True,\n        \"condition\": \"session.state == 'stalled' and session.stall_count >= 1\",\n        \"severity\": \"critical\",\n        \"message\": \"Critical stall: {session_id}\",\n        \"channels\": [\"log\", \"console\", \"email\"]\n    },\n    # Add custom rules\n}\n```\n\n## Monitoring Data Location\n\nAll monitoring data is stored in `~/.openclaw/workspace/.watchdog/`:\n\n- `session_registry.json` - All monitored sessions\n- `monitoring.log` - Monitoring activity logs\n- `metrics.json` - System metrics\n- `incidents.json` - Incident records\n- `alerts.json` - Sent alerts\n- `cron_jobs.json` - Cron job definitions\n\n## Testing Integration\n\nRun the integration test suite:\n\n```bash\ncd ~/.openclaw/workspace\npython3 integration/test_integration.py\n```\n\n## Best Practices\n\n1. **Always register sessions** - Every task >2 minutes should be monitored\n2. **Update activity regularly** - Heartbeat updates every 30-60 seconds\n3. **Include handoff reports** - Sub-agents must provide structured handoff reports\n4. **Monitor cron jobs** - All scheduled tasks should be monitored\n5. **Review alerts regularly** - Check the dashboard for system health\n6. **Integrate with error-learning-loop** - Incidents feed into learning system\n\n## Troubleshooting\n\n### Common Issues\n\n1. **Session not appearing in dashboard**:\n   - Check if session was registered\n   - Verify session state is \"active\"\n   - Check monitoring logs for errors\n\n2. **Alerts not triggering**:\n   - Verify alert rules are enabled\n   - Check alert conditions match session state\n   - Review alerts log file\n\n3. **Cron job monitoring failing**:\n   - Verify cron job is registered\n   - Check execution start/complete calls\n   - Review cron job metrics\n\n### Debug Commands\n\n```bash\n# Check monitoring status\npython3 integration/main_agent_monitoring.py\npython3 integration/subagent_monitoring.py\npython3 integration/cron_monitoring.py\n\n# View monitoring data\ncat ~/.openclaw/workspace/.watchdog/session_registry.json | jq '. | length'\ncat ~/.openclaw/workspace/.watchdog/monitoring.log | tail -20\n\n# Test alerts\npython3 alerts/real_time_alerts.py\n```\n\n## Next Steps\n\n1. **Integrate with existing skills** - Update skills to use monitoring\n2. **Add email alerts** - Configure SMTP for critical alerts\n3. **Create monitoring dashboards** - Web-based monitoring interface\n4. **Implement SLA monitoring** - Track performance against SLAs\n5. **Add resource monitoring** - CPU, memory, disk usage monitoring\n\n## Support\n\nFor issues with monitoring integration:\n1. Check monitoring logs\n2. Review integration test results\n3. Consult this guide\n4. Check AGENTS.md for updated guardrails"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-chat","usage":{"input":527,"output":1825,"cacheRead":47808,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":50160,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773103133005}}
