{"type":"message","id":"6118d2d2","parentId":"3b944b4a","timestamp":"2026-03-10T00:39:53.700Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_4P4d5JiONaBQFE9FcJFNPL4S","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"- **Pattern‑Key**: multi_agent|MULTI_AGENT_HANDOFF|openclaw_subagent|missing_report|handoff_contract_not_enforced\n- **Date**: 2026‑03‑04\n- **Rule**: Every sub‑agent must end its final response with a structured Handoff Report (Outcome + Incidents).\n- **Rationale**: Without enforced reporting, incidents from sub‑agents are lost, breaking the error‑learning loop.\n- **Preflight**: Include Handoff Report requirement in sub‑agent instructions; verify output contains the report.\n\n### Deadlock Detection\n- **Pattern‑Key**: multi_agent|DEADLOCK|progress_starvation|agents_no_progress\n- **Date**: 2026‑03‑05\n- **Rule**: Detect dependency cycles before multi‑agent execution; implement per‑agent timeouts and deadlock resolution.\n- **Rationale**: Agents waiting for each other's outputs can halt entire workflows indefinitely.\n- **Preflight**: Build dependency graph; check for cycles; set individual agent timeouts.\n\n\n\n### alternate_needed\n- **Pattern-Key**: licensing|CONFLICT|feature_requires_license|not_available|alternate_needed\n- **Date**: 2026-03-06\n- **Rule**: Avoid this incident by implementing preventive checks.\n- **Rationale**: Repeated occurrence (count=1) with severity S1.\n- **Preflight**: Check for .\n\n### required\n- **Pattern-Key**: planning|OVERLOAD|decompose|prompt_too_long|required\n- **Date**: 2026-03-06\n- **Rule**: Avoid this incident by implementing preventive checks.\n- **Rationale**: Repeated occurrence (count=1) with severity S2.\n- **Preflight**: Check for .\n\n### cannot_continue\n- **Pattern-Key**: recovery|FAILURE|recovery|resume|checkpoint_missing|cannot_continue\n- **Date**: 2026-03-06\n- **Rule**: Avoid this incident by implementing preventive checks.\n- **Rationale**: Repeated occurrence (count=1) with severity S2.\n- **Preflight**: Check for .\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n### repair_failed\n- **Pattern-Key**: validation|FAILURE|validate|final_output|criteria_not_met|repair_failed\n- **Date**: 2026-03-06\n- **Rule**: Avoid this incident by implementing preventive checks.\n- **Rationale**: Repeated occurrence (count=1) with severity S2.\n- **Preflight**: Check for .\n\n### Watchdog Registration Enforcement\n\n[410 more lines in file. Use offset=300 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773103193691}}
{"type":"message","id":"7bca8802","parentId":"6118d2d2","timestamp":"2026-03-10T00:40:28.426Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Let me add a monitoring integration section to AGENTS.md:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_u6mGpjt6nZy5Thws8RPt12gd","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"~/.openclaw/workspace/AGENTS.md","oldText":"### Watchdog Registration Enforcement\n- **Pattern‑Key**: model|STALL|deepseek-reasoner|no_response|runtime_stuck\n- **Date**: 2026‑03‑06\n- **Rule**: Enforce mandatory watchdog registration for all sub‑agent tasks with expected runtime >5 minutes.\n- **Rationale**: Unregistered long‑running tasks cause stalls that go undetected and unrecovered.\n- **Preflight**: \n  1. Estimate task duration before spawning sub‑agent\n  2. If expected runtime >5 minutes, register with agent‑watchdog immediately after spawn\n  3. Include watchdog registration in standard operating procedure\n  4. Verify registration succeeded before proceeding","newText":"### Watchdog Registration Enforcement\n- **Pattern‑Key**: model|STALL|deepseek-reasoner|no_response|runtime_stuck\n- **Date**: 2026‑03‑06\n- **Rule**: Enforce mandatory watchdog registration for all sub‑agent tasks with expected runtime >5 minutes.\n- **Rationale**: Unregistered long‑running tasks cause stalls that go undetected and unrecovered.\n- **Preflight**: \n  1. Estimate task duration before spawning sub‑agent\n  2. If expected runtime >5 minutes, register with agent‑watchdog immediately after spawn\n  3. Include watchdog registration in standard operating procedure\n  4. Verify registration succeeded before proceeding\n\n## Monitoring System Integration\n\nThe OpenClaw monitoring system is now fully integrated with real monitoring infrastructure. All workflows should include monitoring integration.\n\n### Monitoring Components\n1. **Main Agent Monitoring** (`integration/main_agent_monitoring.py`) - Monitor main agent sessions\n2. **Sub-agent Monitoring** (`integration/subagent_monitoring.py`) - Monitor sub-agent execution  \n3. **Cron Job Monitoring** (`integration/cron_monitoring.py`) - Monitor scheduled tasks\n4. **Real-time Alerts** (`alerts/real_time_alerts.py`) - Alert for critical events\n5. **Monitoring Dashboard** (`dashboard/monitoring_dashboard.py`) - View system health\n\n### Mandatory Monitoring Integration\n\n#### For Main Agent Tasks\n```python\n# At task start\nfrom integration.main_agent_monitoring import main_monitor\nmain_monitor.register_main_agent_session(\n    task_description=\"Task description\",\n    expected_runtime_minutes=10\n)\n\n# During execution (every 30-60 seconds)\nmain_monitor.update_activity(\"Current activity\")\n\n# When spawning sub-agents\nmain_monitor.register_subagent_spawn(\n    subagent_id=\"subagent_123\",\n    task_description=\"Sub-agent task\",\n    expected_runtime_minutes=5\n)\n\n# At task completion\nmain_monitor.complete_session(\n    outcome=\"success\",\n    completion_notes=\"Task completed\"\n)\n```\n\n#### For Sub-agent Tasks\n```python\n# At sub-agent start\nfrom integration.subagent_monitoring import subagent_monitor\nsubagent_monitor.register_subagent_session(\n    task_description=\"Sub-agent task\",\n    expected_runtime_minutes=3,\n    parent_session_id=\"main_session_id\"\n)\n\n# During execution (with progress updates)\nsubagent_monitor.update_activity(\n    activity_description=\"Processing step\",\n    progress_percentage=50\n)\n\n# At completion (with handoff report)\nsubagent_monitor.complete_session(\n    outcome=\"success\",\n    completion_notes=\"Task completed\",\n    handoff_report={\n        \"outcome\": \"success\",\n        \"files_created\": [\"output.txt\"],\n        \"incidents\": [],\n        \"next_actions\": [\"Review results\"]\n    }\n)\n```\n\n#### For Cron Jobs\n```python\n# Register cron job\nfrom integration.cron_monitoring import cron_monitor\njob_id = cron_monitor.register_cron_job(\n    job_name=\"Task Name\",\n    schedule=\"* * * * *\",\n    command=\"task_command\",\n    expected_runtime_minutes=2\n)\n\n# In cron wrapper script\nsession_id = cron_monitor.start_cron_execution(job_id)\n# ... execute task ...\ncron_monitor.complete_cron_execution(\n    job_id,\n    success=True,\n    output=\"Task output\",\n    runtime_seconds=120\n)\n```\n\n### Monitoring Dashboard\nView system health with:\n```bash\npython3 dashboard/monitoring_dashboard.py\n```\n\n### Alert System\nAlerts are automatically generated for:\n- Critical stalls (>5 minutes)\n- Repeated failures (≥3 recovery attempts)\n- Multiple stalled sessions (≥3)\n- Cron job failures\n- High-severity incident clusters\n\n### Monitoring Data Location\nAll monitoring data is stored in `~/.openclaw/workspace/.watchdog/`:\n- `session_registry.json` - Active and historical sessions\n- `monitoring.log` - Monitoring activity\n- `metrics.json` - System metrics\n- `incidents.json` - Incident records\n- `alerts.json` - Sent alerts\n\n### Integration Testing\nTest monitoring integration with:\n```bash\npython3 integration/test_integration.py\n```\n\n### Full Documentation\nSee `integration/MONITORING_INTEGRATION_GUIDE.md` for complete documentation."}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-chat","usage":{"input":579,"output":1160,"cacheRead":50304,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":52043,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773103193698}}
{"type":"message","id":"fd5f5666","parentId":"7bca8802","timestamp":"2026-03-10T00:40:28.445Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_u6mGpjt6nZy5Thws8RPt12gd","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in ~/.openclaw/workspace/AGENTS.md."}],"details":{"diff":"     ...\n 306   2. If expected runtime >5 minutes, register with agent‑watchdog immediately after spawn\n 307   3. Include watchdog registration in standard operating procedure\n 308   4. Verify registration succeeded before proceeding\n 309 \n+310 ## Monitoring System Integration\n+311 \n+312 The OpenClaw monitoring system is now fully integrated with real monitoring infrastructure. All workflows should include monitoring integration.\n+313 \n+314 ### Monitoring Components\n+315 1. **Main Agent Monitoring** (`integration/main_agent_monitoring.py`) - Monitor main agent sessions\n+316 2. **Sub-agent Monitoring** (`integration/subagent_monitoring.py`) - Monitor sub-agent execution  \n+317 3. **Cron Job Monitoring** (`integration/cron_monitoring.py`) - Monitor scheduled tasks\n+318 4. **Real-time Alerts** (`alerts/real_time_alerts.py`) - Alert for critical events\n+319 5. **Monitoring Dashboard** (`dashboard/monitoring_dashboard.py`) - View system health\n+320 \n+321 ### Mandatory Monitoring Integration\n+322 \n+323 #### For Main Agent Tasks\n+324 ```python\n+325 # At task start\n+326 from integration.main_agent_monitoring import main_monitor\n+327 main_monitor.register_main_agent_session(\n+328     task_description=\"Task description\",\n+329     expected_runtime_minutes=10\n+330 )\n+331 \n+332 # During execution (every 30-60 seconds)\n+333 main_monitor.update_activity(\"Current activity\")\n+334 \n+335 # When spawning sub-agents\n+336 main_monitor.register_subagent_spawn(\n+337     subagent_id=\"subagent_123\",\n+338     task_description=\"Sub-agent task\",\n+339     expected_runtime_minutes=5\n+340 )\n+341 \n+342 # At task completion\n+343 main_monitor.complete_session(\n+344     outcome=\"success\",\n+345     completion_notes=\"Task completed\"\n+346 )\n+347 ```\n+348 \n+349 #### For Sub-agent Tasks\n+350 ```python\n+351 # At sub-agent start\n+352 from integration.subagent_monitoring import subagent_monitor\n+353 subagent_monitor.register_subagent_session(\n+354     task_description=\"Sub-agent task\",\n+355     expected_runtime_minutes=3,\n+356     parent_session_id=\"main_session_id\"\n+357 )\n+358 \n+359 # During execution (with progress updates)\n+360 subagent_monitor.update_activity(\n+361     activity_description=\"Processing step\",\n+362     progress_percentage=50\n+363 )\n+364 \n+365 # At completion (with handoff report)\n+366 subagent_monitor.complete_session(\n+367     outcome=\"success\",\n+368     completion_notes=\"Task completed\",\n+369     handoff_report={\n+370         \"outcome\": \"success\",\n+371         \"files_created\": [\"output.txt\"],\n+372         \"incidents\": [],\n+373         \"next_actions\": [\"Review results\"]\n+374     }\n+375 )\n+376 ```\n+377 \n+378 #### For Cron Jobs\n+379 ```python\n+380 # Register cron job\n+381 from integration.cron_monitoring import cron_monitor\n+382 job_id = cron_monitor.register_cron_job(\n+383     job_name=\"Task Name\",\n+384     schedule=\"* * * * *\",\n+385     command=\"task_command\",\n+386     expected_runtime_minutes=2\n+387 )\n+388 \n+389 # In cron wrapper script\n+390 session_id = cron_monitor.start_cron_execution(job_id)\n+391 # ... execute task ...\n+392 cron_monitor.complete_cron_execution(\n+393     job_id,\n+394     success=True,\n+395     output=\"Task output\",\n+396     runtime_seconds=120\n+397 )\n+398 ```\n+399 \n+400 ### Monitoring Dashboard\n+401 View system health with:\n+402 ```bash\n+403 python3 dashboard/monitoring_dashboard.py\n+404 ```\n+405 \n+406 ### Alert System\n+407 Alerts are automatically generated for:\n+408 - Critical stalls (>5 minutes)\n+409 - Repeated failures (≥3 recovery attempts)\n+410 - Multiple stalled sessions (≥3)\n+411 - Cron job failures\n+412 - High-severity incident clusters\n+413 \n+414 ### Monitoring Data Location\n+415 All monitoring data is stored in `~/.openclaw/workspace/.watchdog/`:\n+416 - `session_registry.json` - Active and historical sessions\n+417 - `monitoring.log` - Monitoring activity\n+418 - `metrics.json` - System metrics\n+419 - `incidents.json` - Incident records\n+420 - `alerts.json` - Sent alerts\n+421 \n+422 ### Integration Testing\n+423 Test monitoring integration with:\n+424 ```bash\n+425 python3 integration/test_integration.py\n+426 ```\n+427 \n+428 ### Full Documentation\n+429 See `integration/MONITORING_INTEGRATION_GUIDE.md` for complete documentation.\n+430 \n 310 ### test_incident\n 311 - **Pattern-Key**: memory|FAILURE|backup_creation|file_not_found|test_incident\n 312 - **Date**: 2026-03-09\n 313 - **Rule**: Avoid this incident by implementing preventive checks.\n     ...","firstChangedLine":310},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773103228438}}
{"type":"message","id":"99ea58c2","parentId":"fd5f5666","timestamp":"2026-03-10T00:41:20.869Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now let me create a simple wrapper script for easy monitoring integration:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_SFVRCRSKPZ12WDtZwT0i2hrd","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"~/.openclaw/workspace/monitoring_wrapper.py","content":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"\nMonitoring Wrapper Script\nEasy integration of monitoring into OpenClaw workflows.\n\"\"\"\n\nimport sys\nimport os\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\n# Add workspace to path\nsys.path.insert(0, str(Path.home() / '.openclaw' / 'workspace'))\n\ndef setup_main_agent_monitoring(task_description, expected_runtime_minutes=10):\n    \"\"\"Set up monitoring for main agent task.\"\"\"\n    from integration.main_agent_monitoring import main_monitor\n    \n    print(f\"🔍 Setting up monitoring for: {task_description}\")\n    success = main_monitor.register_main_agent_session(\n        task_description=task_description,\n        expected_runtime_minutes=expected_runtime_minutes\n    )\n    \n    if success:\n        print(f\"✅ Monitoring registered: {main_monitor.session_id}\")\n        return main_monitor.session_id\n    else:\n        print(\"❌ Failed to register monitoring\")\n        return None\n\ndef update_monitoring_activity(activity_description):\n    \"\"\"Update monitoring activity.\"\"\"\n    from integration.main_agent_monitoring import main_monitor\n    \n    if main_monitor.session_id:\n        success = main_monitor.update_activity(activity_description)\n        if success:\n            print(f\"📝 Activity updated: {activity_description}\")\n        else:\n            print(\"⚠️ Failed to update activity\")\n        return success\n    else:\n        print(\"⚠️ No active monitoring session\")\n        return False\n\ndef register_subagent_monitoring(subagent_id, task_description, expected_runtime_minutes=5):\n    \"\"\"Register sub-agent monitoring.\"\"\"\n    from integration.main_agent_monitoring import main_monitor\n    from integration.subagent_monitoring import subagent_monitor\n    \n    # Register with main agent\n    if main_monitor.session_id:\n        success = main_monitor.register_subagent_spawn(\n            subagent_id=subagent_id,\n            task_description=task_description,\n            expected_runtime_minutes=expected_runtime_minutes\n        )\n        if success:\n            print(f\"👥 Sub-agent registered: {subagent_id}\")\n        else:\n            print(\"⚠️ Failed to register sub-agent with main agent\")\n    \n    # Also set up sub-agent monitor\n    subagent_monitor.subagent_id = subagent_id\n    subagent_monitor.parent_session_id = main_monitor.session_id\n    \n    return subagent_monitor\n\ndef complete_monitoring(outcome=\"success\", completion_notes=None):\n    \"\"\"Complete monitoring session.\"\"\"\n    from integration.main_agent_monitoring import main_monitor\n    \n    if main_monitor.session_id:\n        success = main_monitor.complete_session(\n            outcome=outcome,\n            completion_notes=completion_notes\n        )\n        if success:\n            print(f\"✅ Monitoring completed: {outcome}\")\n        else:\n            print(\"⚠️ Failed to complete monitoring\")\n        return success\n    else:\n        print(\"⚠️ No active monitoring session to complete\")\n        return False\n\ndef run_monitoring_dashboard():\n    \"\"\"Run the monitoring dashboard.\"\"\"\n    from dashboard.monitoring_dashboard import MonitoringDashboard\n    \n    print(\"📊 Starting monitoring dashboard...\")\n    dashboard = MonitoringDashboard()\n    dashboard.display_dashboard()\n\ndef check_system_health():\n    \"\"\"Check system health and generate report.\"\"\"\n    from dashboard.monitoring_dashboard import MonitoringDashboard\n    \n    dashboard = MonitoringDashboard()\n    dashboard.load_data()\n    \n    summary = dashboard.data.get(\"summary\", {})\n    \n    print(\"=\" * 60)\n    print(\"System Health Report\")\n    print(\"=\" * 60)\n    \n    print(f\"\\n📈 Sessions:\")\n    print(f\"  Total: {summary.get('total_sessions', 0)}\")\n    print(f\"  Active: {summary.get('active_sessions', 0)}\")\n    print(f\"  Stalled: {summary.get('stalled_sessions', 0)}\")\n    print(f\"  Completed: {summary.get('completed_sessions', 0)}\")\n    \n    print(f\"\\n⏰ Cron Jobs:\")\n    print(f\"  Total: {summary.get('total_cron_jobs', 0)}\")\n    print(f\"  Enabled: {summary.get('enabled_cron_jobs', 0)}\")\n    print(f\"  Success Rate: {summary.get('cron_success_rate', 0):.1f}%\")\n    \n    print(f\"\\n⚠️  Incidents:\")\n    print(f\"  Total: {summary.get('total_incidents', 0)}\")\n    print(f\"  Recent (1h): {summary.get('recent_incidents', 0)}\")\n    \n    print(f\"\\n🔄 Recovery Actions: {summary.get('recovery_actions', 0)}\")\n    \n    # Health status\n    stalled_sessions = summary.get('stalled_sessions', 0)\n    if stalled_sessions == 0:\n        print(f\"\\n✅ System Health: GOOD\")\n    elif stalled_sessions <= 2:\n        print(f\"\\n⚠️  System Health: DEGRADED ({stalled_sessions} stalled sessions)\")\n    else:\n        print(f\"\\n❌ System Health: CRITICAL ({stalled_sessions} stalled sessions)\")\n    \n    print(\"=\" * 60)\n    \n    return summary\n\ndef main():\n    \"\"\"Main function for command-line usage.\"\"\"\n    import argparse\n    \n    parser = argparse.ArgumentParser(description=\"OpenClaw Monitoring Wrapper\")\n    subparsers = parser.add_subparsers(dest=\"command\", help=\"Command to run\")\n    \n    # Setup command\n    setup_parser = subparsers.add_parser(\"setup\", help=\"Set up monitoring for a task\")\n    setup_parser.add_argument(\"description\", help=\"Task description\")\n    setup_parser.add_argument(\"--minutes\", type=int, default=10, help=\"Expected runtime in minutes\")\n    \n    # Update command\n    update_parser = subparsers.add_parser(\"update\", help=\"Update monitoring activity\")\n    update_parser.add_argument(\"activity\", help=\"Activity description\")\n    \n    # Subagent command\n    subagent_parser = subparsers.add_parser(\"subagent\", help=\"Register sub-agent monitoring\")\n    subagent_parser.add_argument(\"id\", help=\"Sub-agent ID\")\n    subagent_parser.add_argument(\"description\", help=\"Task description\")\n    subagent_parser.add_argument(\"--minutes\", type=int, default=5, help=\"Expected runtime in minutes\")\n    \n    # Complete command\n    complete_parser = subparsers.add_parser(\"complete\", help=\"Complete monitoring session\")\n    complete_parser.add_argument(\"--outcome\", default=\"success\", help=\"Outcome (success, partial, failure)\")\n    complete_parser.add_argument(\"--notes\", help=\"Completion notes\")\n    \n    # Dashboard command\n    subparsers.add_parser(\"dashboard\", help=\"Run monitoring dashboard\")\n    \n    # Health command\n    subparsers.add_parser(\"health\", help=\"Check system health\")\n    \n    args = parser.parse_args()\n    \n    if args.command == \"setup\":\n        setup_main_agent_monitoring(args.description, args.minutes)\n    \n    elif args.command == \"update\":\n        update_monitoring_activity(args.activity)\n    \n    elif args.command == \"subagent\":\n        register_subagent_monitoring(args.id, args.description, args.minutes)\n    \n    elif args.command == \"complete\":\n        complete_monitoring(args.outcome, args.notes)\n    \n    elif args.command == \"dashboard\":\n        run_monitoring_dashboard()\n    \n    elif args.command == \"health\":\n        check_system_health()\n    \n    else:\n        parser.print_help()\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    main()"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-chat","usage":{"input":45,"output":1690,"cacheRead":52032,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":53767,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773103228443}}
